3.01	Just_Like_Jesse_James	Just Like Jesse James	"Just Like Jesse James" is a pop rock song by American singer-actress Cher in her twentieth album Heart of Stone. It is the third North American and second European official single release on October 1989 by Geffen Records. The song was written by Desmond Child and Diane Warren. It is a December 1989 top ten hit. The song's title is a reference to Wild West bandit Jesse James.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4f/Cherjljj.jpg/220px-Cherjljj.jpg
